data.name: cvRodolfo
data.value: He holds a post-graduate degree in finance from EPGE-FGV (2001) and an undergraduate degree in Business Administration from Fundação Getulio Vargas - SP (1997). Currently he is the coordinator of the undergraduate course at FFIA - Faculdade FIA ​​de Administração e Negócios, maintained Fundação Instituto de Administração, as well as professor of the Graduate and of the Professional Masters in Business Management of this same institution. Research the following areas: franchising, entrepreneurship, corporate and market finance, complexity theory, risk and related border issues. He has twice been awarded the prize for best academic work of the year on franchises by the Brazilian Franchising Association (ABF) for his doctoral thesis (2015) and his master's dissertation (2012). He was a business consultant at McKinsey & company, an executive in mobile phone, electric power and education companies. He also works as an academic director of MacPoli Professional Courses and collaborates in topics such as entrepreneurship and finance with the magazines PEGN - Small Business & Big Business, Superinteressante and Você SA.

data.name: cvParada
data.value: For more than 30 years, he has been an IT, Project Specialist, Consultant, Entrepreneur and Systems Development Consultant for 14 years as a lecturer at USP, FIA, FAAP and FAM for 6 years in initiatives to foster entrepreneurship and innovation as a teacher , Mentor and entrepreneur. Created and developed the methodology for the guidance of companies and professionals "Descomplicando Carreiras", created and manages the group Amigos Indicam Amigos on facebook that encourages professional relocation. Master's degree in business management, with an MBA in project management and a degree in business administration and systems analysis.

data.value: Systems Architect and Scrum Master, a professional with more than 20 years of experience in project development for the financial and retail market. Graduated in Business Administration and Postgraduate in Architecture of Solutions.
